1
00:00:00,107 --> 00:00:02,617
(Announcement for the 1st Round of Open Pick Voting Results)

2
00:00:02,717 --> 00:00:04,186
(A: Listening Session of Jae Hwan's new song)

3
00:00:04,187 --> 00:00:06,617
(B: Listening Session of the Theme Song)

4
00:00:07,017 --> 00:00:08,556
(Open Pick Voting: From April 28 to April 30)

5
00:00:08,557 --> 00:00:10,016
(46,155 out of 65,294 voters chose Capsule B.)

6
00:00:10,017 --> 00:00:11,286
(Thank you for participating in the voting process.)

7
00:00:11,287 --> 00:00:13,163
(They're enjoying their free time in their own way.)

8
00:00:13,187 --> 00:00:14,496
Do you want to listen to the theme song?

9
00:00:14,497 --> 00:00:16,156
- Great. Let's all listen to it. - Together?

10
00:00:16,157 --> 00:00:19,197
Is that the theme song for our new season?

11
00:00:19,467 --> 00:00:20,537
I can't wait.

12
00:00:20,867 --> 00:00:22,273
- I'm curious. Let's listen to it. - Sounds great.

13
00:00:22,297 --> 00:00:24,636
All right. The title is "WE WANNA GO."

14
00:00:24,637 --> 00:00:26,467
- "WE WANNA GO?" - "We want to go."

15
00:00:26,707 --> 00:00:28,676
"WE WANNA GO."

16
00:00:28,677 --> 00:00:29,677
- I'll play it. - Yes.

17
00:00:30,377 --> 00:00:31,847
Play it loud, so we can all hear it.

18
00:00:33,377 --> 00:00:35,616
(The song starts off with a cheerful beat.)

19
00:00:35,617 --> 00:00:37,217
I like it. It has an energetic start.

20
00:00:37,847 --> 00:00:39,917
(Loving it)

21
00:00:40,217 --> 00:00:41,287
Hey, this is a great song.

22
00:00:41,957 --> 00:00:43,627
(Focused)

23
00:00:44,687 --> 00:00:45,687
Hey!

24
00:00:46,787 --> 00:00:48,327
(Catchy)

25
00:00:48,527 --> 00:00:49,896
"I'm ready now."

26
00:00:49,897 --> 00:00:50,897
The song is catchy.

27
00:00:51,267 --> 00:00:53,837
(Already addicted to the melody)

28
00:00:54,097 --> 00:00:55,097
I love it.

29
00:00:55,637 --> 00:00:57,436
(This is Jae Hwan's part.)

30
00:00:57,437 --> 00:00:59,136
(They listen to the song while checking whose part it is.)

31
00:00:59,137 --> 00:01:00,137
(This is Min Hyun's part.)

32
00:01:00,137 --> 00:01:01,137
(Because I love you)

33
00:01:02,877 --> 00:01:04,276
(It causes a group uprising.)

34
00:01:04,277 --> 00:01:05,606
- Come on. Seriously? - Gosh.

35
00:01:05,607 --> 00:01:07,216
He took the main part like the prince again.

36
00:01:07,217 --> 00:01:08,516
- Come on. Seriously? - Gosh.

37
00:01:08,517 --> 00:01:09,793
- I'm not going to sing it! - Hey.

38
00:01:09,817 --> 00:01:11,917
- Let's not listen to it. - Come on.

39
00:01:12,787 --> 00:01:14,556
(The uprising for the highlight takes place in an instant.)

40
00:01:14,557 --> 00:01:16,233
- I'm not going to sing it. - I won't either.

41
00:01:16,257 --> 00:01:17,586
(He can only smile.)

42
00:01:17,587 --> 00:01:18,587
What is this?

43
00:01:18,588 --> 00:01:20,727
But who's going to sing the highlight if not him?

44
00:01:23,567 --> 00:01:25,727
(Who's going to do it?)

45
00:01:25,867 --> 00:01:27,097
You know what we should do?

46
00:01:27,337 --> 00:01:29,997
Let's battle it out for the highlight.

47
00:01:30,407 --> 00:01:32,727
Will we go around the room and sing it like a competition?

48
00:01:33,037 --> 00:01:35,206
(Candidate 1, Main Rapper Park Woo Jin)

49
00:01:35,207 --> 00:01:36,207
Okay. You're out.

50
00:01:36,477 --> 00:01:38,207
(Disappointed)

51
00:01:39,177 --> 00:01:41,917
(All right then. Is it time for me to step up?)

52
00:01:42,417 --> 00:01:45,317
(King Jae Hwan has descended to the Wanna Base.)

53
00:01:45,547 --> 00:01:46,646
(Candidate 2, Main Vocalist Kim Jae Hwan)

54
00:01:46,647 --> 00:01:48,186
(Because I love you)

55
00:01:48,187 --> 00:01:49,517
(Acting playful)

56
00:01:49,657 --> 00:01:50,787
Because I love you.

57
00:01:51,027 --> 00:01:52,733
(How do you like this innocent vocalist with a sexy voice?)

58
00:01:52,757 --> 00:01:53,927
(A mocking laugh)

59
00:01:54,697 --> 00:01:56,497
(You're laughing at me?)

60
00:01:57,697 --> 00:01:59,167
(Oh, I'm sorry.)

61
00:01:59,297 --> 00:02:01,137
(He actually finds it funny too.)

62
00:02:01,397 --> 00:02:03,357
But this part will stand out if Min Hyun does it.

63
00:02:03,497 --> 00:02:05,037
- You're our only option. - I agree.

64
00:02:05,437 --> 00:02:09,437
(It's perfect for the emperor's look and voice.)

65
00:02:09,807 --> 00:02:11,077
I'll give him that.

66
00:02:11,807 --> 00:02:13,446
This song perfectly describes...

67
00:02:13,447 --> 00:02:15,046
- our show. - Right.

68
00:02:15,047 --> 00:02:16,047
That explains "gotcha" in the lyrics.

69
00:02:16,048 --> 00:02:17,846
Right. "Gotcha" came up a lot in the song.

70
00:02:17,847 --> 00:02:18,847
"Euratgotcha."

71
00:02:19,187 --> 00:02:20,217
I love the song.

72
00:02:20,857 --> 00:02:22,086
It sounds like a song...

73
00:02:22,087 --> 00:02:23,726
a cheerful fifth-generation idol group would sing.

74
00:02:23,727 --> 00:02:25,756
Wanna One is aiming to become a fifth-generation idol group.

75
00:02:25,757 --> 00:02:28,077
(Will they try out to become a 5th-generation idol group?)

76
00:02:38,337 --> 00:02:40,637
(Episode 2: Let's Go and Have Some Real Fun!)

77
00:02:41,337 --> 00:02:43,306
I'm really hungry. Are we not going to eat?

78
00:02:43,307 --> 00:02:44,777
Min Hyun, I'm hungry.

79
00:02:45,247 --> 00:02:48,316
Let's discuss what we're going to do with our meal.

80
00:02:48,317 --> 00:02:49,317
- Okay. - Sounds good.

81
00:02:49,318 --> 00:02:50,587
I want a big meal.

82
00:02:50,787 --> 00:02:52,086
Don't you want a proper meal?

83
00:02:52,087 --> 00:02:53,616
- Should we order food? - Let's do that.

84
00:02:53,617 --> 00:02:54,656
I want pizza.

85
00:02:54,657 --> 00:02:56,017
How about pizza and Chinese food?

86
00:02:56,287 --> 00:02:57,556
Chinese food sounds good.

87
00:02:57,557 --> 00:02:59,326
- Yes. We can share the food. - Like jjajangmyeon?

88
00:02:59,327 --> 00:03:00,926
It's been a while. How about some tangsuyuk?

89
00:03:00,927 --> 00:03:02,657
Hold on. Let me check the app.

90
00:03:03,797 --> 00:03:05,296
(But...)

91
00:03:05,297 --> 00:03:07,667
(who's going to pay for the food?)

92
00:03:08,437 --> 00:03:10,557
(At that moment, a thought crosses Sung Woon's mind.)

93
00:03:11,207 --> 00:03:13,706
(Sung Woon visited Dae Hwi's luxurious house a while ago.)

94
00:03:13,707 --> 00:03:14,867
(He has a lot of money here.)

95
00:03:15,307 --> 00:03:16,636
(He opened up the safe...)

96
00:03:16,637 --> 00:03:18,877
(and checked out the display case.)

97
00:03:19,207 --> 00:03:20,616
(Sung Woon goes back to Dae Hwi's room.)

98
00:03:20,617 --> 00:03:22,977
(I can smell it.)

99
00:03:24,117 --> 00:03:25,986
- Hey, Dae Hwi. - Yes.

100
00:03:25,987 --> 00:03:27,256
- Come here. - What?

101
00:03:27,257 --> 00:03:29,586
There's a card in here. We can use it, right?

102
00:03:29,587 --> 00:03:30,587
(A card?)

103
00:03:30,887 --> 00:03:33,897
(It was nestled among the treasure.)

104
00:03:35,157 --> 00:03:37,327
(A VVIP card for the people in the top 9th percentile)

105
00:03:37,897 --> 00:03:39,066
There's my face on the card.

106
00:03:39,067 --> 00:03:40,996
Right. This is fake.

107
00:03:40,997 --> 00:03:42,666
Sung Woon, what is this? An escape room?

108
00:03:42,667 --> 00:03:43,667
Well...

109
00:03:44,137 --> 00:03:45,666
- Look. - Sung Woon.

110
00:03:45,667 --> 00:03:47,276
- Hey! It opens. - Did you...

111
00:03:47,277 --> 00:03:48,636
- No. - Take it out.

112
00:03:48,637 --> 00:03:49,637
Pull it.

113
00:03:49,638 --> 00:03:50,647
Sung Woon.

114
00:03:50,977 --> 00:03:52,306
You look like a robber.

115
00:03:52,307 --> 00:03:54,147
Hold on. There's something about this card.

116
00:03:54,677 --> 00:03:55,947
No way.

117
00:03:56,217 --> 00:03:57,986
- Wait. Is that a real card? - I told you. See?

118
00:03:57,987 --> 00:03:59,346
It says a VIP card. This one is fake.

119
00:03:59,347 --> 00:04:00,693
- But this one must be real. - This... I see.

120
00:04:00,717 --> 00:04:03,187
(This is the real one.)

121
00:04:03,557 --> 00:04:05,587
Guys!

122
00:04:06,057 --> 00:04:07,456
Don't worry about money.

123
00:04:07,457 --> 00:04:09,656
We found a card inside Dae Hwi's room.

124
00:04:09,657 --> 00:04:10,966
- There was a card. - A platinum card.

125
00:04:10,967 --> 00:04:13,097
Really? How?

126
00:04:13,267 --> 00:04:15,666
- We can just pay with this card. - We can pay with this.

127
00:04:15,667 --> 00:04:17,436
- It was in your room, Dae Hwi? - Yes.

128
00:04:17,437 --> 00:04:20,067
We can order the food and ask to pay on site.

129
00:04:20,207 --> 00:04:21,767
But this isn't my personal card, right?

130
00:04:22,177 --> 00:04:23,536
Do you want to go on an overnight getaway...

131
00:04:23,537 --> 00:04:25,207
- to Japan with this? - Should we?

132
00:04:25,277 --> 00:04:26,347
Sounds good.

133
00:04:26,747 --> 00:04:27,747
- After we eat, - I like that.

134
00:04:27,748 --> 00:04:28,776
We can leave right away.

135
00:04:28,777 --> 00:04:29,816
Let's go to Fukuoka.

136
00:04:29,817 --> 00:04:31,446
- We can visit a hot spring. - Yes.

137
00:04:31,447 --> 00:04:32,716
We can sleep in a ryokan.

138
00:04:32,717 --> 00:04:33,717
Sounds good.

139
00:04:33,718 --> 00:04:35,717
Should we tell you our order now?

140
00:04:36,117 --> 00:04:38,126
- Five stir-fried jjajangmyeon. - Five.

141
00:04:38,127 --> 00:04:41,127
- Half and half. - We'll get the half and half pizza.

142
00:04:41,727 --> 00:04:43,966
(Wanna One starts exploring the Wanna Base...)

143
00:04:43,967 --> 00:04:46,167
(while they wait for their lunch.)

144
00:04:46,827 --> 00:04:47,837
(Spotting something)

145
00:04:48,637 --> 00:04:49,873
(Sung Woon brings a board game from the activity zone.)

146
00:04:49,897 --> 00:04:51,736
Hey! Listen up. Let's play this game.

147
00:04:51,737 --> 00:04:53,706
And the loser can't eat tangsuyuk. What do you think?

148
00:04:53,707 --> 00:04:57,646
Sung Woon. A whole pizza pie has eight slices.

149
00:04:57,647 --> 00:04:59,106
- The loser can't eat the pizza. - Sounds good.

150
00:04:59,107 --> 00:05:00,146
That's good.

151
00:05:00,147 --> 00:05:01,147
Right?

152
00:05:01,477 --> 00:05:03,786
(They will play the Pop-up Pirate...)

153
00:05:03,787 --> 00:05:06,047
(to decide who can't eat pizza.)

154
00:05:06,447 --> 00:05:08,186
- How will we decide the loser? - With this?

155
00:05:08,187 --> 00:05:10,186
If his head pops up on your turn, you can't eat pizza then.

156
00:05:10,187 --> 00:05:11,187
(The pirate?)

157
00:05:11,327 --> 00:05:12,787
But this one looks really fun.

158
00:05:13,187 --> 00:05:14,896
This could end in one turn, though.

159
00:05:14,897 --> 00:05:15,897
(Ringing)

160
00:05:15,898 --> 00:05:16,957
- What? - What?

161
00:05:18,197 --> 00:05:19,197
(Reacting to the doorbell ringing...)

162
00:05:19,197 --> 00:05:20,197
- Our food is here! - I'll get the food.

163
00:05:20,197 --> 00:05:21,197
(like Pavlov's dogs)

164
00:05:21,198 --> 00:05:22,936
- Let's eat. - Let's do this.

165
00:05:22,937 --> 00:05:24,537
I'm starving.

166
00:05:25,507 --> 00:05:26,566
Did we already pay?

167
00:05:26,567 --> 00:05:28,076
- I need the card. - The card.

168
00:05:28,077 --> 00:05:30,307
- This is the one, right? - Yes. Thank you.

169
00:05:30,847 --> 00:05:32,077
(Staggering)

170
00:05:36,277 --> 00:05:37,286
(Chaotic)

171
00:05:37,287 --> 00:05:38,917
What's wrong with them?

172
00:05:39,817 --> 00:05:42,917
- Hey! Let go of me! - Ji Hoon.

173
00:05:43,587 --> 00:05:44,856
(Gosh, Ji Hoon...)

174
00:05:44,857 --> 00:05:46,387
(You're having fun, aren't you?)

175
00:05:46,757 --> 00:05:48,496
Ji Hoon is having a lot of fun here.

176
00:05:48,497 --> 00:05:49,497
Ji Hoon...

177
00:05:50,097 --> 00:05:51,197
He looks happy here.

178
00:05:52,967 --> 00:05:55,467
(Me?)

179
00:05:55,497 --> 00:05:56,997
(He's so adorable.)

180
00:05:57,207 --> 00:05:58,307
- Ji Hoon. - Seriously.

181
00:05:58,637 --> 00:05:59,866
He looks like King Danjong.

182
00:05:59,867 --> 00:06:01,077
- He does. - He...

183
00:06:01,677 --> 00:06:04,276
He only stayed in the palace. But he came out to the village.

184
00:06:04,277 --> 00:06:07,447
(The 17-year-old Hong Wi is enjoying his days in Gwangcheon Valley.)

185
00:06:07,617 --> 00:06:10,097
(While the members are feeling emotional like his subjects...)

186
00:06:10,617 --> 00:06:11,816
- Thank you. - Thank you.

187
00:06:11,817 --> 00:06:14,116
- Thank you. Gosh. - Thank you. The card...

188
00:06:14,117 --> 00:06:16,257
- We'll pay with this card. - Okay.

189
00:06:17,057 --> 00:06:18,627
What if this doesn't work?

190
00:06:19,187 --> 00:06:20,187
What if...

191
00:06:20,897 --> 00:06:22,356
(The card is already in his hand.)

192
00:06:22,357 --> 00:06:23,357
I don't know if it works.

193
00:06:25,127 --> 00:06:27,737
(Dae Hwi nervously watches him.)

194
00:06:28,067 --> 00:06:29,096
(The transaction feels like forever.)

195
00:06:29,097 --> 00:06:30,136
(Let's see.)

196
00:06:30,137 --> 00:06:32,567
- Is it not working? - Wait. Give it a second.

197
00:06:33,037 --> 00:06:34,777
(Will it work?)

198
00:06:34,977 --> 00:06:35,977
(The transaction was successful.)

199
00:06:35,978 --> 00:06:37,206
- Thank you. - Thank you.

200
00:06:37,207 --> 00:06:38,606
Hey, we couldn't have eaten without Dae Hwi.

201
00:06:38,607 --> 00:06:39,607
Right.

202
00:06:39,608 --> 00:06:42,517
(I'm the card owner of the Wanna Base.)

203
00:06:42,717 --> 00:06:44,086
Our food is here!

204
00:06:44,087 --> 00:06:46,186
- It's food! - Yes!

205
00:06:46,187 --> 00:06:48,286
Guys, let's pick the loser with this and then eat.

206
00:06:48,287 --> 00:06:49,727
- Okay. Let's pick the loser. - Yes.

207
00:06:50,057 --> 00:06:51,786
If his head pops up on your turn, you're the loser.

208
00:06:51,787 --> 00:06:53,787
- Okay. He can't eat the pizza. - Right, he can't.

209
00:06:55,097 --> 00:06:56,097
You passed.

210
00:06:56,098 --> 00:06:59,397
Wait. Come on. Let's do it once everyone gets here.

211
00:06:59,867 --> 00:07:04,807
(Rummaging through)

212
00:07:05,767 --> 00:07:06,907
Woo Jin, do it again.

213
00:07:07,477 --> 00:07:09,207
- Wait. I passed. - No. Do it again.

214
00:07:10,177 --> 00:07:12,257
(The chirpy birdie eats a piece of tangsuyuk first.)

215
00:07:12,507 --> 00:07:14,177
(Booing at him)

216
00:07:14,277 --> 00:07:16,346
- This is for the pizza. - No. But still.

217
00:07:16,347 --> 00:07:17,617
(How dare you?)

218
00:07:17,747 --> 00:07:20,216
The older ones haven't eaten yet. How could you eat first?

219
00:07:20,217 --> 00:07:21,487
He's doing whatever he wants.

220
00:07:22,287 --> 00:07:23,356
(This bet was for the pizza.)

221
00:07:23,357 --> 00:07:24,427
(Feeling wronged)

222
00:07:25,087 --> 00:07:26,187
(Darn it.)

223
00:07:29,597 --> 00:07:30,597
Seriously.

224
00:07:32,997 --> 00:07:33,997
That's it.

225
00:07:35,997 --> 00:07:40,437
(The loser is chosen in one turn.)

226
00:07:40,977 --> 00:07:42,137
(That's it.)

227
00:07:44,377 --> 00:07:46,606
- That's it. - You totally deserved it.

228
00:07:46,607 --> 00:07:49,076
- You deserved it. - Okay.

229
00:07:49,077 --> 00:07:50,716
- How did that happen? - You can't eat pizza.

230
00:07:50,717 --> 00:07:51,947
He lost the game right away.

231
00:07:52,687 --> 00:07:53,746
- See? - You can't eat pizza.

232
00:07:53,747 --> 00:07:55,456
You totally deserved it.

233
00:07:55,457 --> 00:07:56,916
Right. You shouldn't have eaten the tangsuyuk without us.

234
00:07:56,917 --> 00:07:58,026
Hey, you can't eat pizza now.

235
00:07:58,027 --> 00:08:00,256
- Gosh. I knew this would happen. - Goodness.

236
00:08:00,257 --> 00:08:01,626
- Thank you for the food. - Thank you for the food.

237
00:08:01,627 --> 00:08:03,796
- Thank you for the food. - Enjoy the food.

238
00:08:03,797 --> 00:08:05,426
Guys, don't spill food on the floor.

239
00:08:05,427 --> 00:08:06,596
- Okay. - Okay.

240
00:08:06,597 --> 00:08:08,197
- This looks good. - Of course.

241
00:08:08,267 --> 00:08:09,947
I haven't had Chinese food in a long time.

242
00:08:10,197 --> 00:08:14,877
(They get to have lunch together after a long time.)

243
00:08:16,077 --> 00:08:17,877
- Their jjajangmyeon is so good. - It's good.

244
00:08:18,577 --> 00:08:19,577
We picked a great restaurant.

245
00:08:19,578 --> 00:08:21,017
Hey, try this tangsuyuk.

246
00:08:22,147 --> 00:08:23,147
How is it, Min Hyun?

247
00:08:23,148 --> 00:08:24,587
(A man is clearly feeling gloomy.)

248
00:08:25,187 --> 00:08:26,316
(Diet)

249
00:08:26,317 --> 00:08:27,857
(My diet is very important.)

250
00:08:28,117 --> 00:08:29,857
(I'm crazy about my diet now.)

251
00:08:30,057 --> 00:08:31,427
What's all this?

252
00:08:31,557 --> 00:08:36,657
(Jae Hwan said he'd be on a strict diet before his comeback.)

253
00:08:36,927 --> 00:08:38,297
Jae Hwan, how about Chinese food?

254
00:08:38,467 --> 00:08:40,767
I brought my own food. I need to stick to my diet.

255
00:08:41,067 --> 00:08:42,667
I have to stick to my diet.

256
00:08:42,767 --> 00:08:44,766
- Really? - I'm like the gym coach.

257
00:08:44,767 --> 00:08:47,553
(Jae Hwan kept mentioning his diet as if he was brainwashing himself.)

258
00:08:47,577 --> 00:08:49,936
(The food is right in front of him, )

259
00:08:49,937 --> 00:08:53,777
(but he can only sniffle.)

260
00:08:54,817 --> 00:08:58,246
(Despite the temptations the world throws at him, )

261
00:08:58,247 --> 00:09:02,016
(the dedicated dieter only thinks about sticking to his diet.)

262
00:09:02,017 --> 00:09:04,057
(What?)

263
00:09:09,157 --> 00:09:10,157
- It's good. - Is it good?

264
00:09:10,158 --> 00:09:11,167
(Humming in approval)

265
00:09:11,267 --> 00:09:14,296
(He happily hums away, pleased by the worldly flavor.)

266
00:09:14,297 --> 00:09:16,737
(Humming in approval)

267
00:09:18,437 --> 00:09:20,136
(The dedicated dieter...)

268
00:09:20,137 --> 00:09:22,207
(becomes a dedicated foodie.)

269
00:09:22,477 --> 00:09:23,577
It's pizza.

270
00:09:24,207 --> 00:09:25,807
But this is huge.

271
00:09:26,277 --> 00:09:27,546
Let's open it up.

272
00:09:27,547 --> 00:09:28,946
(Ta-da)

273
00:09:28,947 --> 00:09:30,277
(His mouth is full of food.)

274
00:09:31,347 --> 00:09:33,016
- This pizza is huge. - Yes.

275
00:09:33,017 --> 00:09:34,916
I ordered a double extra large pizza on purpose.

276
00:09:34,917 --> 00:09:36,616
- Then Woo Jin can eat too. - He might be able to eat it.

277
00:09:36,617 --> 00:09:38,127
(Paying attention)

278
00:09:38,157 --> 00:09:39,456
Woo Jin lost the game. He can't.

279
00:09:39,457 --> 00:09:41,296
Even if we have to throw it out, he can't eat this.

280
00:09:41,297 --> 00:09:43,996
(Even if we have to throw it out, he can't eat this.)

281
00:09:43,997 --> 00:09:45,166
(Horrified by the next-level cruelty)

282
00:09:45,167 --> 00:09:46,196
He's so cruel.

283
00:09:46,197 --> 00:09:47,327
Gosh, seriously.

284
00:09:47,767 --> 00:09:49,797
- We have exactly eight slices. - Right.

285
00:09:50,437 --> 00:09:51,937
I'm not going to eat it.

286
00:09:52,007 --> 00:09:53,567
(Chuckling)

287
00:09:53,867 --> 00:09:55,337
Woo Jin is sulking.

288
00:09:55,607 --> 00:09:56,977
I would've cried if I were him.

289
00:09:57,407 --> 00:09:58,407
(Sniffing)

290
00:09:58,577 --> 00:09:59,577
Smell it.

291
00:09:59,578 --> 00:10:01,176
Hey.

292
00:10:01,177 --> 00:10:02,716
What was that? He tried to take a bite.

293
00:10:02,717 --> 00:10:04,617
- I was letting him smell it. - Only just that?

294
00:10:06,317 --> 00:10:08,187
(Torturing him with the smell from both sides)

295
00:10:12,027 --> 00:10:13,687
(Gobbling it up)

296
00:10:14,197 --> 00:10:15,457
You ate it, didn't you?

297
00:10:15,697 --> 00:10:18,166
Jin Young spilled cheese, so I ate it off the floor.

298
00:10:18,167 --> 00:10:19,296
I'll allow it.

299
00:10:19,297 --> 00:10:20,643
Anything on the floor is fair game.

300
00:10:20,667 --> 00:10:21,667
(Concerned)

301
00:10:21,668 --> 00:10:22,737
Woo Jin.

302
00:10:23,537 --> 00:10:24,967
Woo Jin, should I drop mine?

303
00:10:26,107 --> 00:10:27,107
(Shaking)

304
00:10:28,107 --> 00:10:29,607
(Innocent)

305
00:10:29,737 --> 00:10:32,106
He's scary in a sweet kind of way.

306
00:10:32,107 --> 00:10:33,883
(Sweet Hwang takes care of Woo Jin in a scary, yet sweet way.)

307
00:10:33,907 --> 00:10:35,747
- He's a psychopath. - Yes, he is.

308
00:10:37,117 --> 00:10:39,217
- I'm stuffed. - There's more.

309
00:10:39,517 --> 00:10:41,486
Let's play a game for the cleanup.

310
00:10:41,487 --> 00:10:43,156
Wait. There's a game I want to play.

311
00:10:43,157 --> 00:10:44,157
- What is it? - I saw it earlier.

312
00:10:44,157 --> 00:10:45,157
Let's play it.

313
00:10:45,158 --> 00:10:47,826
I saw this on social media all the time.

314
00:10:47,827 --> 00:10:49,526
I always wanted to try it.

315
00:10:49,527 --> 00:10:51,396
You throw the sticky patches...

316
00:10:51,397 --> 00:10:53,196
- onto the wall. - Right.

317
00:10:53,197 --> 00:10:55,036
- The first patch to fall loses. - Right.

318
00:10:55,037 --> 00:10:57,096
- Sure. Let's do it. - Do we have nine patches, though?

319
00:10:57,097 --> 00:10:58,566
One, two, three...

320
00:10:58,567 --> 00:10:59,836
There are only seven.

321
00:10:59,837 --> 00:11:01,477
- Then we should... - No. Or...

322
00:11:01,637 --> 00:11:03,376
(What should we do?)

323
00:11:03,377 --> 00:11:04,676
Do we have two more of these?

324
00:11:04,677 --> 00:11:06,347
(Do we have two more of these?)

325
00:11:06,947 --> 00:11:08,177
Who are you talking to?

326
00:11:08,777 --> 00:11:10,897
We're the only ones here. Why do you keep doing that?

327
00:11:11,217 --> 00:11:12,217
Father.

328
00:11:13,017 --> 00:11:14,047
(Father!)

329
00:11:14,857 --> 00:11:16,557
(Summoning the Almighty for a toy)

330
00:11:17,087 --> 00:11:18,187
"Amen."

331
00:11:18,887 --> 00:11:20,326
(Sacredly performing the Sign of Cross)

332
00:11:20,327 --> 00:11:21,626
- Father. - Brother.

333
00:11:21,627 --> 00:11:23,257
I'd like two more of these.

334
00:11:23,527 --> 00:11:25,927
Might I get two more, please?

335
00:11:26,127 --> 00:11:27,867
- "Please?" - "Please?"

336
00:11:28,037 --> 00:11:31,006
Father, could we get...

337
00:11:31,007 --> 00:11:32,967
- just two more? - I...

338
00:11:33,067 --> 00:11:34,877
I guess not. Let's go tournament-style.

339
00:11:35,077 --> 00:11:37,747
(The sticky battle begins for the cleanup.)

340
00:11:37,807 --> 00:11:39,407
- No! - Hey!

341
00:11:39,707 --> 00:11:41,316
Could I get a pair of pants?

342
00:11:41,317 --> 00:11:42,317
What's this?

343
00:11:42,318 --> 00:11:43,598
(The losers clean up afterward.)

344
00:11:43,917 --> 00:11:45,787
(After their first meal at the Wanna Base...)

345
00:11:47,217 --> 00:11:48,357
This is fascinating.

346
00:11:49,557 --> 00:11:50,557
(Ta-da)

347
00:11:51,587 --> 00:11:53,087
Wait. This is heavy.

348
00:11:53,187 --> 00:11:54,467
- I hope we get clothes. - Okay!

349
00:11:56,997 --> 00:11:57,997
(Pouring out)

350
00:11:58,767 --> 00:12:01,367
(We'll return the school uniforms. Give us comfy indoor clothes.)

351
00:12:01,767 --> 00:12:02,966
(His wish comes true.)

352
00:12:02,967 --> 00:12:05,667
(Indoor clothes are prepared for their comfort.)

353
00:12:06,067 --> 00:12:07,513
- This looks like a prison uniform. - It is.

354
00:12:07,537 --> 00:12:09,307
It's a prison uniform.

355
00:12:09,777 --> 00:12:10,906
We've worn this before.

356
00:12:10,907 --> 00:12:12,246
- We have? - There are no pants.

357
00:12:12,247 --> 00:12:14,776
(They wore this standard home outfit at the Zero Base too.)

358
00:12:14,777 --> 00:12:16,146
(This looks like a prison uniform.)

359
00:12:16,147 --> 00:12:18,447
(He even said the same thing about the outfit.)

360
00:12:19,147 --> 00:12:20,147
(This outfit holds many memories.)

361
00:12:20,148 --> 00:12:22,957
(So we prepared the same outfit this time.)

362
00:12:23,457 --> 00:12:24,526
(Zero Base in 2017)

363
00:12:24,527 --> 00:12:25,986
(Jin Young, Min Hyun, Ji Sung, Jae Hwan, Seong Wu, Dae Hwi)

364
00:12:25,987 --> 00:12:26,987
(Wanna Base in 2026)

365
00:12:26,988 --> 00:12:28,573
(Jin Young, Min Hyun, Ji Sung, Jae Hwan, Seong Wu, Dae Hwi)

366
00:12:28,597 --> 00:12:31,157
(They're sitting in the same spots, dressed in the same outfit.)

367
00:12:32,167 --> 00:12:33,467
It feels like I'm dreaming.

368
00:12:35,297 --> 00:12:36,437
- Right. - It does, right?

369
00:12:36,797 --> 00:12:37,867
Back to the future.

370
00:12:38,607 --> 00:12:41,237
I think we were at Sangam only an hour ago.

371
00:12:41,707 --> 00:12:44,577
It's crazy how we came here, had a meal, and are digesting the food.

372
00:12:45,377 --> 00:12:48,677
Chilling here with everyone feels surreal.

373
00:12:48,777 --> 00:12:49,876
I had never pictured this.

374
00:12:49,877 --> 00:12:51,786
- I just thought that... - Right.

375
00:12:51,787 --> 00:12:54,217
Our journey together was over then.

376
00:12:54,917 --> 00:12:57,287
It's so crazy that we got to do this another season.

377
00:12:57,957 --> 00:12:59,586
It's amazing how we all had time for this.

378
00:12:59,587 --> 00:13:02,657
I'm also grateful everyone tried to work out their schedule for this.

379
00:13:03,357 --> 00:13:05,126
I'm happy that everyone wanted to do this together.

380
00:13:05,127 --> 00:13:06,167
Totally.

381
00:13:06,627 --> 00:13:08,367
There's always a right time for things.

382
00:13:09,297 --> 00:13:10,797
And I guess it's now.

383
00:13:12,367 --> 00:13:14,307
We all wanted to get together again like this.

384
00:13:15,407 --> 00:13:18,477
(Wanna One is spending time again together after going separate ways.)

385
00:13:18,947 --> 00:13:20,147
Shall we start the chat?

386
00:13:20,747 --> 00:13:22,647
Shall we communicate with the Plus Chat?

387
00:13:23,017 --> 00:13:24,487
Let's gather up and do it together.

388
00:13:24,887 --> 00:13:26,687
Let's ask them if they went home safely.

389
00:13:27,087 --> 00:13:28,687
If they caught a cold on their way home.

390
00:13:28,757 --> 00:13:30,717
- It's the Chat Room, right? - Yes, that's right.

391
00:13:31,457 --> 00:13:33,556
(We invite you to the Wanna One Chat Coom.)

392
00:13:33,557 --> 00:13:35,097
(Warning: They talk too much.)

393
00:13:35,297 --> 00:13:36,557
Who will start?

394
00:13:36,697 --> 00:13:38,043
(The youngest member starts the chat.)

395
00:13:38,067 --> 00:13:39,867
(Dae Hwi says, "Did you all go home safely?")

396
00:13:40,027 --> 00:13:41,266
There's "reply" here.

397
00:13:41,267 --> 00:13:43,137
- Fans can reply to the chat. - Right.

398
00:13:43,567 --> 00:13:45,707
- Right. - Gosh, so many fans are chatting.

399
00:13:46,107 --> 00:13:48,777
(Sung Woon sings for Wannables.)

400
00:13:48,877 --> 00:13:52,176
(Sung Woon takes selfies for Wannables.)

401
00:13:52,177 --> 00:13:53,706
(He took a close shot not to show the Wanna Base behind.)

402
00:13:53,707 --> 00:13:55,147
(But his uniform is in the selfie.)

403
00:13:55,417 --> 00:13:56,877
Sung Woon, no spoilers, okay?

404
00:13:56,977 --> 00:13:58,147
But this is okay, isn't it?

405
00:13:58,887 --> 00:14:00,617
We won't hide it forever anyway.

406
00:14:00,987 --> 00:14:02,356
(Ji Hoon is chatting with the Wannables.)

407
00:14:02,357 --> 00:14:03,717
(I miss you already.)

408
00:14:04,487 --> 00:14:06,656
Ji Hoon, you're the only one who's being so sweet.

409
00:14:06,657 --> 00:14:08,296
- I know. - Ji Hoon must think...

410
00:14:08,297 --> 00:14:09,777
that this is a personal chatting app.

411
00:14:10,057 --> 00:14:11,727
Ji Hoon, do as others do.

412
00:14:12,597 --> 00:14:13,827
- Hey, Min Hyun. - Yes?

413
00:14:14,167 --> 00:14:16,767
What was the name of your character?

414
00:14:16,997 --> 00:14:18,236
- Yoon Ga Min. - Yong Gam Yi?

415
00:14:18,237 --> 00:14:19,766
- It's Yoon. Yoon Ga Min. - Yong Gam Yi?

416
00:14:19,767 --> 00:14:21,507
- Yoon Gam? - Yoon Ga Min.

417
00:14:21,737 --> 00:14:22,936
- Ga Min? - Yes.

418
00:14:22,937 --> 00:14:24,983
(Sung Woon wants to see Yoon Ga Min and Yeon Si Eun fight.)

419
00:14:25,007 --> 00:14:28,147
You win if you don't give Ji Hoon a pen, right?

420
00:14:28,247 --> 00:14:30,476
Ga Min uses the forbidden skills he learned from his uncle.

421
00:14:30,477 --> 00:14:32,463
(Yeon Si Eun with a watergun is just being happy.)

422
00:14:32,487 --> 00:14:35,217
(Wannables talk about this for a while.)

423
00:14:35,557 --> 00:14:37,387
(Two men who never lose meet.)

424
00:14:37,587 --> 00:14:38,787
(They meet at the Wanna Base.)

425
00:14:38,957 --> 00:14:41,257
(A fight with their pride on the line)

426
00:14:41,457 --> 00:14:42,997
(The result will be revealed soon.)

427
00:14:43,597 --> 00:14:44,637
(Mr. Ong joins the fight.)

428
00:14:45,227 --> 00:14:46,597
What's up with Seong Wu?

429
00:14:46,997 --> 00:14:48,757
Someone says, "Ong Seong Wu is just a fool."

430
00:14:48,897 --> 00:14:50,617
"Ong Seong Wu is just a fool?" Where is it?

431
00:14:50,897 --> 00:14:53,066
- It was in the comments. - "Seong Wu is just a fool."

432
00:14:53,067 --> 00:14:56,076
- Seong Wu. Write a reply to it. - That's so wrong.

433
00:14:56,077 --> 00:14:58,577
That's so harsh. I'll find that comment.

434
00:14:58,777 --> 00:15:00,546
They're asking to change our profile photo.

435
00:15:00,547 --> 00:15:01,947
I see. So we can change it.

436
00:15:02,177 --> 00:15:03,677
I'll use Seung Wu's old photo.

437
00:15:04,277 --> 00:15:05,717
You'll use my old photo?

438
00:15:06,347 --> 00:15:08,657
Your funny photo. Sleeping like this.

439
00:15:09,257 --> 00:15:10,616
(Ong avenges right away.)

440
00:15:10,617 --> 00:15:12,787
(Taking funny pictures of Min Hyun)

441
00:15:12,927 --> 00:15:13,957
I'll use this.

442
00:15:14,757 --> 00:15:16,196
Go ahead.

443
00:15:16,197 --> 00:15:17,533
(The two born in 1995 are having fun as always.)

444
00:15:17,557 --> 00:15:19,027
- Sung Woon. - Yes?

445
00:15:19,097 --> 00:15:20,537
Can I use this for my profile photo?

446
00:15:21,027 --> 00:15:22,196
(Laughing)

447
00:15:22,197 --> 00:15:23,497
That's too harsh.

448
00:15:23,697 --> 00:15:24,706
(Let me see.)

449
00:15:24,707 --> 00:15:27,367
This is a legendary funny photo of him.

450
00:15:27,437 --> 00:15:28,437
But I don't mind.

451
00:15:28,777 --> 00:15:30,137
I thought that picture was pretty.

452
00:15:30,577 --> 00:15:32,077
Gosh, I can't do that.

453
00:15:32,307 --> 00:15:33,347
Goodness. Look at this.

454
00:15:33,877 --> 00:15:35,617
Gosh, that's so long ago.

455
00:15:35,817 --> 00:15:36,877
We took that in the van?

456
00:15:37,017 --> 00:15:38,287
We were so young back then.

457
00:15:38,487 --> 00:15:40,747
(Touched)

458
00:15:41,117 --> 00:15:43,416
- Gosh, Plus Chat is fun. - I know.

459
00:15:43,417 --> 00:15:44,426
(Their first chat with the Wannables ends.)

460
00:15:44,427 --> 00:15:46,587
Do you want to play a game? Red Light, Green Light.

461
00:15:46,687 --> 00:15:48,257
Okay. It's Red Light, Green Light.

462
00:15:48,457 --> 00:15:49,826
Okay. I'll only go after one guy.

463
00:15:49,827 --> 00:15:51,196
(Game 1: Red Light, Green Light)

464
00:15:51,197 --> 00:15:52,527
- I'll start. - Okay.

465
00:15:53,397 --> 00:15:56,296
Red light,

466
00:15:56,297 --> 00:15:57,497
green light!

467
00:15:58,767 --> 00:16:00,107
Green light!

468
00:16:00,407 --> 00:16:01,906
Min Hyun, come over here.

469
00:16:01,907 --> 00:16:03,476
(He quickly tries to grab Jin Young.)

470
00:16:03,477 --> 00:16:05,277
(Bae Bae pulls back his leg.)

471
00:16:06,107 --> 00:16:07,107
Come here, Min Hyun.

472
00:16:07,108 --> 00:16:08,916
(Sorry, Min Hyun.)

473
00:16:08,917 --> 00:16:09,946
There's nothing you can do now.

474
00:16:09,947 --> 00:16:10,977
Red light, green light!

475
00:16:11,287 --> 00:16:12,617
(Stopping)

476
00:16:12,747 --> 00:16:13,947
He's smiling back there.

477
00:16:14,347 --> 00:16:15,757
Red light, green light.

478
00:16:16,317 --> 00:16:18,187
(He's trying to take the easy way.)

479
00:16:18,987 --> 00:16:21,747
(How dare you? I won't let you do that even if you're older than me.)

480
00:16:22,057 --> 00:16:23,796
(His whole body shakes as the king targets him.)

481
00:16:23,797 --> 00:16:25,667
- Come here, Ji Sung. - Come.

482
00:16:25,797 --> 00:16:28,767
Hey, it's not fair. Ji Hoon here...

483
00:16:29,367 --> 00:16:30,696
(Glancing)

484
00:16:30,697 --> 00:16:32,307
- Come here. - Red light...

485
00:16:33,637 --> 00:16:34,806
(Running faster and more skillfully)

486
00:16:34,807 --> 00:16:36,336
(Somebody save Jirung!)

487
00:16:36,337 --> 00:16:38,577
(The first game is over.)

488
00:16:38,877 --> 00:16:41,946
(Game 2: Ddakji)

489
00:16:41,947 --> 00:16:44,116
(Game 3: Large Yutnori)

490
00:16:44,117 --> 00:16:46,816
(They play games nonstop.)

491
00:16:46,817 --> 00:16:48,116
(They play 3 games in a row.)

492
00:16:48,117 --> 00:16:49,856
(They're done with all the games now.)

493
00:16:49,857 --> 00:16:50,857
(Or so we thought.)

494
00:16:50,858 --> 00:16:52,556
- Let's play a game. - Great.

495
00:16:52,557 --> 00:16:53,557
What do you want to play?

496
00:16:53,558 --> 00:16:54,896
Let's play a really fun one.

497
00:16:54,897 --> 00:16:56,156
The Noisy Zombie Game.

498
00:16:56,157 --> 00:16:58,296
What are the rules for the Noisy Zombie Game?

499
00:16:58,297 --> 00:17:00,866
- Let me... - Explain the rules.

500
00:17:00,867 --> 00:17:01,966
- How do you play it? - It's going to be really fun.

501
00:17:01,967 --> 00:17:03,196
- Go ahead. - Explain the game.

502
00:17:03,197 --> 00:17:04,566
- We'll wear the slippers. - Okay.

503
00:17:04,567 --> 00:17:06,367
It will make sounds whenever we walk.

504
00:17:06,937 --> 00:17:09,836
The rest of us must run away with the squeaky slippers on.

505
00:17:09,837 --> 00:17:12,476
And the tagger will wear a blindfold and have a squeaky hammer.

506
00:17:12,477 --> 00:17:13,776
The tagger will follow the sound...

507
00:17:13,777 --> 00:17:15,076
- To hit us with the hammer? - to hit them with the hammer.

508
00:17:15,077 --> 00:17:16,917
Then the tagged ones will be the zombies.

509
00:17:17,147 --> 00:17:18,347
Okay.

510
00:17:18,647 --> 00:17:19,647
Should we clear this area?

511
00:17:19,648 --> 00:17:20,928
- Sure. - It could be dangerous.

512
00:17:21,047 --> 00:17:23,207
- Hey, Woo Jin. Clear the area. - That's for our meal.

513
00:17:24,057 --> 00:17:25,157
(They're ready!)

514
00:17:25,487 --> 00:17:27,187
Guys, let's put on the slippers.

515
00:17:27,727 --> 00:17:29,607
- We all have to wear them, right? - All right.

516
00:17:29,997 --> 00:17:31,877
(It's starting to get noisy at the Wanna Base.)

517
00:17:32,697 --> 00:17:34,266
Gosh, listen to this.

518
00:17:34,267 --> 00:17:35,573
(The squeaky slippers are indeed noisy.)

519
00:17:35,597 --> 00:17:36,696
