00:26:53,127 --> 00:26:54,187
Like this?

788
00:26:54,657 --> 00:26:56,496
(Ji Hoon!)

789
00:26:56,497 --> 00:26:58,667
(Ji Sung!)

790
00:27:01,197 --> 00:27:03,966
(Let's stop.)

791
00:27:03,967 --> 00:27:05,337
Come on.

792
00:27:06,107 --> 00:27:07,237
Get some sleep.

793
00:27:07,567 --> 00:27:10,037
- You're not going to take a nap? - No, I'll be fine.

794
00:27:10,407 --> 00:27:11,476
You won't join me?

795
00:27:11,477 --> 00:27:13,076
No, I'm good.

796
00:27:13,077 --> 00:27:14,306
- Ji Sung. - No.

797
00:27:14,307 --> 00:27:15,747
I can't sleep by myself.

798
00:27:16,847 --> 00:27:19,517
No, you slept like a baby with your mouth open in the car.

799
00:27:20,247 --> 00:27:21,817
Stop lying. You were sleeping...

800
00:27:22,157 --> 00:27:23,517
- with your mouth open. - Ji Sung.

801
00:27:23,717 --> 00:27:25,786
- You were supposed to say yes. - Really?

802
00:27:25,787 --> 00:27:29,027
You should have helped me fall asleep...

803
00:27:29,297 --> 00:27:30,297
and leave.

804
00:27:30,997 --> 00:27:32,097
Hold on.

805
00:27:32,297 --> 00:27:33,726
- Wait. - No.

806
00:27:33,727 --> 00:27:35,736
- No. Okay. - I'll help you fall asleep.

807
00:27:35,737 --> 00:27:37,736
- Okay. - You'll go out like a light. Wait.

808
00:27:37,737 --> 00:27:38,737
I'm sleepy now.

809
00:27:38,738 --> 00:27:40,537
(It worked like a charm.)

810
00:27:40,837 --> 00:27:42,136
Sleep tight.

811
00:27:42,137 --> 00:27:43,853
(I'll go to sleep for real now. No more goofing around.)

812
00:27:43,877 --> 00:27:46,376
(Ji Hoon, sleep tight.)

813
00:27:46,377 --> 00:27:47,457
(He's going to take a nap?)

814
00:27:49,177 --> 00:27:50,676
(What are you doing here?)

815
00:27:50,677 --> 00:27:51,716
Come on out.

816
00:27:51,717 --> 00:27:53,686
- Why? - You can't already take a nap.

817
00:27:53,687 --> 00:27:55,686
- Come out. Just this once. - I'm going to take a nap.

818
00:27:55,687 --> 00:27:58,587
- What are you doing? - Just this once.

819
00:27:58,657 --> 00:28:00,856
(Ji Hoon is dragged out and can't take a nap in the end.)

820
00:28:00,857 --> 00:28:02,096
What? I thought you were going to take a nap.

821
00:28:02,097 --> 00:28:03,656
He woke me up.

822
00:28:03,657 --> 00:28:05,657
- What do you think? - You wanted him to see this?

823
00:28:06,427 --> 00:28:08,166
Our food is here!

824
00:28:08,167 --> 00:28:10,566
But the table is too small for all of us.

825
00:28:10,567 --> 00:28:12,467
We should hold up our plate, I guess.

826
00:28:12,937 --> 00:28:13,937
Should I make one?

827
00:28:14,437 --> 00:28:16,477
(Putting on a safety vest and a helmet is a must!)

828
00:28:17,407 --> 00:28:18,806
Let's make chairs and a table.

829
00:28:18,807 --> 00:28:20,076
So it's easier for us to eat here.

830
00:28:20,077 --> 00:28:21,953
Once I finish, this is going to feel rewarding.

831
00:28:21,977 --> 00:28:23,047
(Hammering)

832
00:28:23,277 --> 00:28:24,747
I'm using up my forearm muscles.

833
00:28:24,847 --> 00:28:27,986
I'm going to build everything before dinner.

834
00:28:27,987 --> 00:28:30,757
(He doesn't play games with them and focuses on his project.)

835
00:28:30,887 --> 00:28:31,887
(Glancing)

836
00:28:32,787 --> 00:28:34,286
What? I want to play too.

837
00:28:34,287 --> 00:28:36,156
(Mumbling to himself)

838
00:28:36,157 --> 00:28:38,866
(Manager Park's living room is completed with his hard work.)

839
00:28:38,867 --> 00:28:39,867
We can clap for him three times.

840
00:28:39,868 --> 00:28:41,226
Clap three times now.

841
00:28:41,227 --> 00:28:42,797
(Feeling proud of his complete project)

842
00:28:43,497 --> 00:28:45,707
I'm done with those disturbers.

843
00:28:46,807 --> 00:28:49,577
Let me get some sleep now.

844
00:28:50,977 --> 00:28:53,676
(Winking Cutie, sleep tight.)

845
00:28:53,677 --> 00:28:55,516
Hello, everyone!

846
00:28:55,517 --> 00:28:57,247
Hello, everyone!

847
00:28:57,647 --> 00:28:59,416
Hello, everyone!

848
00:28:59,417 --> 00:29:00,646
- Hello. - Hello.

849
00:29:00,647 --> 00:29:02,056
Where are we?

850
00:29:02,057 --> 00:29:03,687
- Wanna Base! - WANNA ONE GO!

851
00:29:03,857 --> 00:29:07,656
We're at the Wanna Base!

852
00:29:07,657 --> 00:29:09,526
Ji Hoon just went to sleep.

853
00:29:09,527 --> 00:29:10,656
He must hate this.

854
00:29:10,657 --> 00:29:12,127
(Forever tortured by MC Ong)

855
00:29:12,267 --> 00:29:13,427
Ji Hoon.

856
00:29:13,997 --> 00:29:15,297
Are you asleep?

857
00:29:15,567 --> 00:29:16,567
(He's hilarious.)

858
00:29:16,568 --> 00:29:17,636
(He's super sleepy.)

859
00:29:17,637 --> 00:29:19,967
Are you asleep, Ji Hoon?

860
00:29:20,767 --> 00:29:22,637
Are you having a sweet dream?

861
00:29:23,307 --> 00:29:25,646
Make some noise if you're asleep.

862
00:29:25,647 --> 00:29:27,246
(Laughing)

863
00:29:27,247 --> 00:29:29,716
(Unintentionally engaging his ab muscles by laughing hard)

864
00:29:29,717 --> 00:29:31,846
(They're driving me crazy.)

865
00:29:31,847 --> 00:29:33,717
How can he do that if he's asleep?

866
00:29:34,217 --> 00:29:35,593
(What he said makes him laugh too.)

867
00:29:35,617 --> 00:29:37,916
Make some noise if you're asleep.

868
00:29:37,917 --> 00:29:39,356
Yes!

869
00:29:39,357 --> 00:29:40,986
(Please let me sleep!)

870
00:29:40,987 --> 00:29:42,796
- He did it. - He did it.

871
00:29:42,797 --> 00:29:43,957
He did scream.

872
00:29:44,127 --> 00:29:46,167
(Thank you for playing along.)

873
00:29:46,427 --> 00:29:51,967
(I'm really going to get some sleep now.)

874
00:29:52,437 --> 00:29:55,737
(The other members are recharging their energy too.)

875
00:29:56,977 --> 00:29:58,137
I'm kind of hungry.

876
00:29:58,537 --> 00:29:59,546
Me too.

877
00:29:59,547 --> 00:30:01,053
- Talking makes me hungry. - Let's eat something.

878
00:30:01,077 --> 00:30:02,117
Do you want fried chicken?

879
00:30:02,277 --> 00:30:03,877
(Fried chicken?)

880
00:30:03,977 --> 00:30:05,823
(A while ago, they were chatting with Wannables.)

881
00:30:05,847 --> 00:30:07,463
(Dae Hwi, what are you getting for dinner? Fried chicken?)

882
00:30:07,487 --> 00:30:09,416
I'm craving fried chicken now. Do you want to get that for dinner?

883
00:30:09,417 --> 00:30:10,956
- Totally. - How about fried chicken and beer?

884
00:30:10,957 --> 00:30:12,237
- Sounds great. - I'd love that.

885
00:30:12,827 --> 00:30:14,356
(Typing)

886
00:30:14,357 --> 00:30:15,456
(Recommend a dish for our dinner.)

887
00:30:15,457 --> 00:30:16,556
(Jae Hwan is asking Wannables for a dinner recommendation.)

888
00:30:16,557 --> 00:30:18,997
We decided to get fried chicken with beer.

889
00:30:19,467 --> 00:30:21,587
Jae Hwan, they told you to focus on the conversation.

890
00:30:21,827 --> 00:30:24,667
Jae Hwan. They told you to focus on the conversation.

891
00:30:24,937 --> 00:30:26,166
- Let's eat something. - Shall we eat fried chicken?

892
00:30:26,167 --> 00:30:27,506
- Is there fried chicken? - Let's eat it.

893
00:30:27,507 --> 00:30:28,906
I'll prepare it.

894
00:30:28,907 --> 00:30:30,536
- Really? - Fried chicken and beer?

895
00:30:30,537 --> 00:30:31,936
- But fried chicken... - We decided to enjoy them today.

896
00:30:31,937 --> 00:30:33,707
That sounds good. Fried chicken, let's go.

897
00:30:34,207 --> 00:30:35,616
Crispy fried chicken?

898
00:30:35,617 --> 00:30:36,617
That sounds good.

899
00:30:36,618 --> 00:30:38,338
I love fried chicken that's totally crispy.

900
00:30:38,687 --> 00:30:41,116
When you deep-fry this in an air fryer,

901
00:30:41,117 --> 00:30:43,017
it's as good as the delivery fried chicken.

902
00:30:43,257 --> 00:30:45,357
- The delivery fried chicken? - That's right.

903
00:30:45,527 --> 00:30:48,157
(Cook Hwang's meticulous skills)

904
00:30:49,597 --> 00:30:50,597
(Put it in the air fryer and it's done!)

905
00:30:50,598 --> 00:30:52,326
Do you just cook it in there? Is that all?

906
00:30:52,327 --> 00:30:53,327
Really?

907
00:30:54,067 --> 00:30:56,036
- Okay. - I can't wait.

908
00:30:56,037 --> 00:30:57,667
(Wait for a short while!)

909
00:30:58,067 --> 00:30:59,536
During our Wanna One days,

910
00:30:59,537 --> 00:31:01,036
we couldn't enjoy fried chicken and beer...

911
00:31:01,037 --> 00:31:02,976
- since some members were underage. - Right.

912
00:31:02,977 --> 00:31:04,707
Now, all of them have grown up.

913
00:31:05,177 --> 00:31:07,477
We can enjoy fried chicken and beer. It's nice.

914
00:31:09,577 --> 00:31:10,877
I don't think he has grown up.

915
00:31:12,947 --> 00:31:14,516
Just ten minutes ago, he was passed out.

916
00:31:14,517 --> 00:31:15,887
He came back alive.

917
00:31:16,717 --> 00:31:19,163
(Coca-Cola and fried chicken suit Woo Jin, the kindergartener.)

918
00:31:19,187 --> 00:31:21,187
(Meanwhile, Ji Hoon is sleeping.)

919
00:31:21,687 --> 00:31:23,757
(The second-oldest member is resting for real.)

920
00:31:24,797 --> 00:31:27,527
(At that moment, a delicious smell spreads in Wanna Base.)

921
00:31:28,097 --> 00:31:29,637
(I recognize this smell!)

922
00:31:30,367 --> 00:31:31,597
Sung Woon woke up.

923
00:31:31,937 --> 00:31:33,507
(A tasty smell wakes him up.)

924
00:31:34,067 --> 00:31:35,167
Sung Woon.

925
00:31:36,237 --> 00:31:37,306
(Fried chicken party gets 1 more member.)

926
00:31:37,307 --> 00:31:38,876
- What's this? Frozen chicken? - It's cooking.

927
00:31:38,877 --> 00:31:41,606
It becomes very crispy in an air fryer or an oven.

928
00:31:41,607 --> 00:31:42,777
How crispy?

929
00:31:42,917 --> 00:31:44,547
It might peel the roof of your mouth.

930
00:31:44,817 --> 00:31:46,617
Wouldn't that be dangerous?

931
00:31:49,357 --> 00:31:50,587
It's all done.

932
00:31:52,387 --> 00:31:54,057
- No way. - My goodness.

933
00:31:54,427 --> 00:31:55,626
Min Hyun.

934
00:31:55,627 --> 00:31:56,696
(Cook Hwang has prepared...)

935
00:31:56,697 --> 00:31:57,726
(this golden fried chicken.)

936
00:31:57,727 --> 00:31:59,026
- I hear... - It looks incredible.

937
00:31:59,027 --> 00:32:00,726
We need to eat it right away.

938
00:32:00,727 --> 00:32:01,887
I hear the deep-frying sound.

939
00:32:02,027 --> 00:32:03,297
Let's eat.

940
00:32:03,937 --> 00:32:06,336
It's nice that everyone is old enough for beer.

941
00:32:06,337 --> 00:32:09,207
You're right. I was underage back in the day.

942
00:32:09,477 --> 00:32:11,083
(Leader Yoon commemorates it right away.)

943
00:32:11,107 --> 00:32:13,453
- "Chicken and beer as adults." - "Chicken and beer as adults."

944
00:32:13,477 --> 00:32:14,576
- In 1, 2, 3. - Fried chicken.

945
00:32:14,577 --> 00:32:17,117
- Okay. Thank you for the food. - Thank you for the food.

946
00:32:17,717 --> 00:32:19,487
- It's delicious. - It's good.

947
00:32:19,817 --> 00:32:20,817
What? Hey.

948
00:32:20,818 --> 00:32:22,286
- It's so tasty. - It's crispy.

949
00:32:22,287 --> 00:32:23,486
How is it so tender inside?

950
00:32:23,487 --> 00:32:24,886
You must've had it delivered.

951
00:32:24,887 --> 00:32:27,786
Don't lie. Give us proof that you've made it in the air fryer.

952
00:32:27,787 --> 00:32:29,526
- I would've loved it in the army. - Had it been sold at the army...

953
00:32:29,527 --> 00:32:31,357
It'd get sold out every day.

954
00:32:31,527 --> 00:32:32,726
- That's right. It'd be gone. - Seriously.

955
00:32:32,727 --> 00:32:33,997
First-come, first-served.

956
00:32:34,267 --> 00:32:35,696
Fried chicken that gets sold in a frozen state...

957
00:32:35,697 --> 00:32:37,336
usually gets oily and soggy.

958
00:32:37,337 --> 00:32:38,636
Hey, what do you know?

959
00:32:38,637 --> 00:32:40,083
I know quite a lot about the chicken.

960
00:32:40,107 --> 00:32:41,737
(Why are they arguing again?)

961
00:32:42,107 --> 00:32:44,976
Have you had frozen fried chicken in the army?

962
00:32:44,977 --> 00:32:46,646
You can get it outside the army, okay?

963
00:32:46,647 --> 00:32:47,746
Where have you tried it?

964
00:32:47,747 --> 00:32:49,346
You can get it at any mart.

965
00:32:49,347 --> 00:32:50,676
- Do you eat it? - Of course, I do.

966
00:32:50,677 --> 00:32:52,416
- Cheers. Let's wake Ji Hoon up. - Cheers.

967
00:32:52,417 --> 00:32:53,487
That's a good idea.

968
00:32:53,747 --> 00:32:55,347
(What?)

969
00:32:56,387 --> 00:32:57,856
- Where did my cup go? - Where did it go?

970
00:32:57,857 --> 00:32:58,927
Here.

971
00:32:59,257 --> 00:33:00,587
(Flustered)

972
00:33:01,657 --> 00:33:03,227
It's mine.

973
00:33:04,357 --> 00:33:05,526
Thank you for the food.

974
00:33:05,527 --> 00:33:07,687
(The fried chicken and beer party at Wanna Base ends!)

975
00:33:13,407 --> 00:33:15,137
Wannable, you've waited for a long time.

976
00:33:35,227 --> 00:33:37,196
We had planned to drink today,

977
00:33:37,197 --> 00:33:40,926
- so I brought a nice liquor. - Really?

978
00:33:40,927 --> 00:33:42,166
Can I bring it out now?

979
00:33:42,167 --> 00:33:44,367
- Sure. Let's drink it. - Of course.

980
00:33:44,837 --> 00:33:46,366
(On a meaningful note, he brings out the top-shelf liquor.)

981
00:33:46,367 --> 00:33:47,767
- Gosh, what's that? - My goodness.

982
00:33:48,307 --> 00:33:49,867
- Is that a nice liquor? - What's this?

983
00:33:49,907 --> 00:33:51,207
Actually, this liquor is...

984
00:33:51,477 --> 00:33:53,347
(What about it?)

985
00:33:53,407 --> 00:33:55,516
- from Kuan Lin. - What?

986
00:33:55,517 --> 00:33:56,517
What?

987
00:33:56,518 --> 00:33:57,917
(Surprised)

988
00:33:58,117 --> 00:34:00,717
He gifted it so that the members could drink together.

989
00:34:00,887 --> 00:34:02,787
- Really? - Gosh, Kuan Lin.

990
00:34:03,517 --> 00:34:05,857
(While the members had the first get-together, )

991
00:34:06,757 --> 00:34:09,597
(Sung Woon traveled to meet Kuan Lin.)

992
00:34:10,197 --> 00:34:11,226
Kuan Lin!

993
00:34:11,227 --> 00:34:12,566
(They reunited after 7 years.)

994
00:34:12,567 --> 00:34:13,697
Kuan Lin!

995
00:34:13,897 --> 00:34:16,397
(That was when he got the liquor from Kuan Lin.)

996
00:34:16,597 --> 00:34:18,467
- Gosh, Kuan Lin. Thank you. - Is it for us?

997
00:34:18,597 --> 00:34:19,967
I'm so thankful for Kuan Lin.

998
00:34:20,367 --> 00:34:22,307
What? Seong Wu.

999
00:34:22,777 --> 00:34:23,937
(What's this sound?)

1000
00:34:24,077 --> 00:34:25,776
What?

1001
00:34:25,777 --> 00:34:26,906
- It's Kuan Lin! - What?

1002
00:34:26,907 --> 00:34:27,907
(No way.)

1003
00:34:27,977 --> 00:34:29,576
- Sung Woon! - Let's go.

1004
00:34:29,577 --> 00:34:30,977
(Is it Kuan Lin?)

1005
00:34:31,277 --> 00:34:32,347
Jae Hwan!

1006
00:34:32,517 --> 00:34:33,947
- Seong Wu! - What?

1007
00:34:34,087 --> 00:34:35,117
Jae Hwan!

1008
00:34:35,317 --> 00:34:36,887
- Seong Wu! - What?

1009
00:34:37,087 --> 00:34:39,787
(Did Kuan Lin come to Wanna Base?)

1010
00:34:40,887 --> 00:34:42,227
- What? - Jae Hwan!

1011
00:34:43,597 --> 00:34:44,627
What?
